(iii)  Environmental Engineer – Supervision  (domestic). The consultant will 

(a)  review  best  practice  in  the  water  supply,  sanitation  and  solid  waste 
management; 
(b)  certify quality of works, physical progress, bill of quantities, and approval 
of payment to the contractors; 
(c)  help  with  public  participation  and  awareness  programs  including 
involvement of local administrations, civic bodies, NGOs, and the public; 
(d)  generally support ADB’s extended tsunami recovery program, and 
(e)  undertake medium term invitations to bid, and evaluation of bids. 

(iv)  Civil Engineer – Transport (international and domestic). The consultant will 

(a)  prepare  detailed  assessments  with  verification  of  damages  and  cost 
estimates based on unit costs; 
(b)  prepare overall project implementation schedule for different subprojects 
to ensure economy and efficiency in the procurement process; 
(c)  review  required  specifications  of  equipment  for  navigation  aids, 
communications and airport maintenance; 
(d)  manage procurement for all subprojects, including preparation of tender 
documents, evaluation, and award of bids; 
(e)  develop and monitor accounting procedures and subproject accounts; 
(f)  provide engineering assistance, including survey and design—the design 
and  tender  documents  provided  will  be  reviewed  to  ensure  their 
adequateness for the purpose of the Project and to be free of any major 
omissions or errors;  
(g)  supervise  construction,  and  ensure  that  the  works  are  constructed  in 
accordance with contractual requirements; 
(h)  certify quality of works, physical progress, bill of quantities, and approval 
of payment to the contractors; 
(i)  certify conformity, supervise installation, and verify operational condition 
of technical equipment procured under the Project; 
(j)  report progress to and coordinate with the PMU; and 
(k)  assess human resources development needs in MTCA and provide on-
the-job training for MTCA staff to strengthen their capacity. 

